          "",
          "",
          "LAB"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "When you want to know the law, you call a lawyer. When you want to know the rules, you call upon a parliamentarian. Although, to be fair, you started life as a lawyer. But you quickly found your passion was not in arguing the law (or bending it, or breaking it), it was simply knowing it. Knowing order and procedure, knowing protocol and regulation. You switched tracks and became what is known as a Parliamentarian: an expert in order from chaos and structure from collapse. You knew the Rules of Robert backwards and forwards, inside and out. You even served as a Senatorial Parliamentarian, explaining to Senators why they couldn’t do what they were trying to do.  Which is undoubtedly how you attracted the eye of your sire, Barbara Harwick. She had a keen eye and you were exactly what she needed to keep her court running smoothly.  She spent her year and day teaching you, and then pulled every string she could to get you appointed Keeper. You informed Prince and pauper, Primogen and whip alike in how Philadelphia was going to be running from now on (and that would be by the book, thank you).  It wasn’t until The Troubles that you were displaced, something you’d rather not speak of. But now you find yourself in Los Angeles, and maybe - just maybe - with a Ventrue Prince, you can find yourself back in the Keeper’s seat."
        ],
